{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/41587", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/41587/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/41587/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/41587/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/41587", "id": 224882675, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUyMjQ4ODI2NzU=", "number": 41587, "title": "rustc_errors doesn't check terminal attributes correctly", "user": {"login": "keringar", "id": 8889510, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjg4ODk1MTA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8889510?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar", "html_url": "https://github.com/keringar", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2017-04-27T19:05:07Z", "updated_at": "2017-05-13T20:11:35Z", "closed_at": "2017-05-13T20:11:35Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Looking at https://github.com/rust-lang-nursery/rustfmt/issues/1180, I found it originated in syntex_errors, which is basically a stabilized version of https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/master/src/librustc_errors/emitter.rs#L1362. \r\n\r\nLooking over this code, the emitter doesn't check if the terminal actually supports the attribute before trying to set it. For example, in ```apply_style```, ```start_attr``` is called with ```term::Attr::Bold```. But on Windows, the terminal doesn't support bold (https://github.com/Stebalien/term/blob/master/src/win.rs#L181). So whenever an error is encountered, it panics because Bold is not supported. This also affects a Arch Linux + eshell, which doesn't support any attributes at all, including resetting them. As a result, ```t.attr(attr)?``` returns ```term::NotSupported``` which gets returned until it eventually panics at https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/master/src/librustc_errors/emitter.rs#L1067.\r\n\r\nI have a fix for syntex, https://github.com/serde-rs/syntex/pull/121/commits/7ca0bb2e2dbae42d3983991787857730854336ef, that would also work here.", "closed_by": {"login": "keringar", "id": 8889510, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjg4ODk1MTA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8889510?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar", "html_url": "https://github.com/keringar", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/keringar/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/41587/reaction